outline-description =
    Outline is an open-source team knowledge base and wiki with a beautiful, intuitive interface.

    It supports real-time collaborative editing, Markdown, rich embeds, and a powerful
    search engine. Teams use it for documentation, runbooks, meeting notes, and internal
    wikis. Users sign in via Kanidm OIDC — no separate accounts needed.

outline-features =
    - Real-time collaborative editing
    - Markdown with rich formatting
    - Nested document structure
    - Full-text search across all documents
    - OIDC single sign-on via Kanidm
    - Public and private collections
    - Slack, Figma, and other embed integrations
    - PostgreSQL-backed for durability
